Offices include a kindergarten, understood by the architects
The Avriopoint administrative building in Brno is the new headquarters of Arch.Design.
No one would expect to also hide a mini-school with everything that belongs to it - with colored walls, imaginative furniture, a bunch of toys and even a miniature playground on the outdoor terrace.
Since October last year, the children of employees of Arch.Design can visit it.
The architectural and design company Arch.Design, from whose studios came a number of important buildings in Brno, has been counting on space for its company mini-school since the first drawings of the Avriopoint building.
It employs almost 90 people, mostly at the age of a baby boomer, and it was important for women designers and architects to get back to work quickly.
Along with the possibility of shortened appointments, the kindergarten is a benefit that Arch.Design offers to its employees within the social program.
Builders and architects thus have the opportunity to combine demanding employment with childcare.
The mini-school was invented by the employees of Arch.Design and with the support of the management, they managed to obtain a grant from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The company mini-school is financed from the European Social Fund through the Operational Programme of Human Resources and Employment and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the grant funding (a grant of CZK 2.8 million) they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and ensure qualified personnel and operations for two years.
After the financial subsidy is exhausted (2 years), Arch.Design has an obligation to operate a mini-school for 3 years at its own expense.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and the application for the grant was significantly assisted by Economy Rating.
The care is provided by qualified staff, the nurse and the teacher of the school nurses take care of the children all day, so children can go to kindergarten without age restrictions, yet most of them are over 3 years old.
Because it is a "mini-schooler", only 5 children can be present at the same time, but during the day they are replaced by more.
The operation of the kindergarten is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use the kindergarten regardless of the hierarchy of position in the company.
Although it is an individual education and care, the program filling in a mini-school is comparable to the framework program of pre-school education.
Children not only play here, but they are also provided with quality teaching - from basic knowledge to preparation for school benches, English is also taught.
The class is equipped not only with toys, stimulating games, but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of young children directly in the company creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can check their child at any time and get rid of stressful situations with delayed pick-up of children from kindergartens away from their parents’ workplace.
Parents are making more productive use of their working hours.
It is no wonder that there is a naturally loyal employee-employer relationship here.
Arch.Design has thus joined the Czech companies that offer a significant benefit in recruiting new employees, are family-friendly and through this program has strengthened personal marketing.
