The essential elements of the reconstruction were the abolition of all right angles and straight lines and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with the modern concept of connecting spaces.
The social part can be completely connected by opening the living room doors, and a larger company can communicate comfortably together without at the same time maintaining the privacy necessary for more intimate conversations.
In addition to the new fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade, the house with Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s reconstruction also received an unconventional roof and two additional floors.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play is also impressive with light, blue and white glazed tiles, with which the inner courtyard is lined, and light bulbs.
